Paper: hep-th/0210226

Date: 2002-10-23

Title: The renormalisation bialgebra and operads

Authors: Pepijn van der Laan and Ieke Moerdijk

Comments: 2 pages

In a recent preprint, Brouder and Schmitt give a careful construction of a`renormalisation' Hopf algebra out of an arbitrary bialgebra. In this note, wepoint out that this is a special case of the construction of the cooperad of abialgebra (Berger-Moerdijk) combined with the construction of a bialgebra froma cooperad (Frabetti-Van der Laan).